  "prompt": "Why can't I see views on my Instagram videos?",
  "response": "There could be several reasons why you're unable to see views on your Instagram videos:\n\n1. **Privacy Settings**: If your account is private, only your approved followers will be able to see and interact with your videos. This may affect the visibility of views to other users.\n\n2. **Technical Glitches**: Instagram occasionally experiences bugs or glitches that can affect the functionality of the app. If you recently uploaded a video and can't see the views, it might just be a temporary issue.\n\n3. **App Updates**: If your app is out of date, you might encounter various issues, including not seeing view counts. Make sure you have the latest version of Instagram installed.\n\n4. **Content Type**: Make sure you're looking at the right type of content. For example, if it's a story, views are displayed differently, and if it's an Instagram Reel, there may be a delay in showing the view count.\n\n5. **Account Type**: If you are using a personal account, you might not be able to see insights like account type users do with a business or creator account.\n\n6. **Network Issues**: Sometimes network connectivity issues can prevent certain elements from loading properly in the app.\n\n7. **Recent Upload**: If you've just uploaded the video, it might take some time for the views to be processed and displayed.\n\nIf you're still having trouble, try restarting the app, clearing the cache, or checking Instagram's help center for any ongoing issues.",
